This article is a background briefing on the upcoming North American Leaders' Summit. The speakers, identified as "senior administration officials," discuss the importance of the summit in revitalizing relationships with Canada and Mexico. The focus of the summit will be on economic cooperation, COVID-19 response, climate crisis, and migration management. Some of the deliverables expected to be announced include vaccine sharing, updates to the North American Plan for Animal and Pandemic Influenza, and commitments to reduce methane emissions and enhance renewable energy development. The officials also mention discussions on energy reforms in Mexico and the "Remain in Mexico" program, but note that these issues will not be the main focus of the summit. The officials emphasize the importance of regional collaboration and addressing root causes of migration. The article concludes with a Q&A session where the officials respond to questions about vaccine sharing, energy reforms, migration, and other regional issues.